comment_data.body: no comments at all? not even a small shitstorm?

I tried your implementation, everything works well except the... design xD.
I'm gonna make some mockups for the design and put that in form of view/fragments files if you wish.

Anyway, great job. I'll try to compile it soon, once i succeeded at compiling another android app (NewPipe) ^^

EDIT: Oh and when making an audio call from Antox to TRiFA, it makes Antox to crash, and TRiFA with it c:

Well, firstly, what you have there is not a reference implementation of toxcore, it's java binding to c toxcore.

Secondly, [we already have java bindings to c toxcore](https://github.com/TokTok/jvm-toxcore-c), so what is the point of making yet another one?
@SkyzohKey dont make mockups please, just tweak the files in "res/" and do it for real.

>@nurupo if you mean jvm-c-toxcore. its not really usable without scala.

No, I meant what I said -- jvm-toxcore-c. You are confusing jvm-toxcore-api and jvm-toxcore-c. jvm-toxcore-c has no Scala code. Did you not look into existing Java bindings before writing your own?
@nurupo yes it did, i compiled it and talked to iphy alot. no matter now, its done

I'm running Android 7.0 too, my laptop isn't enough powerful to run 1 virtual device, sorry. 

@nurupo At least this one compiles on my laptop, where it never was the case with Antox ðŸ˜‚

>i tried making a test app with it and did not succeed. also i wanted to know where the problems with Antox are. in toxore, in jvmtoxcore or in antox.

Ok, just making sure you know that we already have java bindings to c toxcore. It would suck if you didn't know they exist and wasted your time on writing them.

>@nurupo At least this one compiles on my laptop, where it never was the case with Antox :joy:

Yeah, sadly not all software is easy to compile.
Finally there is a scala-free binding to c-toxcore, woohoo! Please, keep going

@SkyzohKey can you try it now (same link above), it should work on android 7.0
audio is only sent for now (not recevied yet!)

>No, I meant what I said -- jvm-toxcore-c. You are confusing jvm-toxcore-api and jvm-toxcore-c. jvm-toxcore-c has no Scala code. Did you not look into existing Java bindings before writing your own?

My mistake, looks like jvm-toxcore-c does have scala code, I wasn't looking in the right place.
What do you think about generating a Java interface using Swig? Furthermore, Swig would be appropriate to generate bindings for Python, C#, Ruby, Lua, PHP, and other languages as well.
Looks like this is done now.
